Class TestForKeyword

java.lang.Object
koopa.core.parsers.ParserCombinator

koopa.core.grammars.combinators.TestProgramText
koopa.core.grammars.combinators.TestForKeyword
public class TestForKeyword extends TestProgramText
This ParserCombinator tests whether the text matched by a given parser is a keyword or not. Clients can configure which case (keyword or not) should have this parser accept the input.

    • matchesProgramText

      protected boolean matchesProgramText(Parse parse, String text)
      Description copied from class: TestProgramText
      To be implemented by subclasses, this is equivalent to ParserCombinator.accepts(Parse), but passes along the contents of all matched tokens which are accepted by Grammar.isProgramText(Data).

      This will not get called if the TestProgramText.parser did not match.
